<button class="mt-2 text-xs underline text-slate-600" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="lumen-data-table">Show data table (the chart as a table)</button>
<div class="mt-2 flex items-end gap-2 flex-wrap">
<span class="text-xs text-slate-500">Add external benchmark (reading-fluency norms):</span>
<label class="text-xs text-slate-600 flex flex-col">Grade<input type="number" class="w-16 px-2 py-1 border rounded" value=""/>
</label>
<label class="text-xs text-slate-600 flex flex-col">Season<select class="px-2 py-1 border rounded">
<option value="fall">fall</option>
<option value="winter" selected="">winter</option>
<option value="spring">spring</option>
</select>
</label>
<button class="px-2 py-1 text-xs rounded border border-teal-600 text-teal-700 hover:bg-teal-50">Add</button>
</div>
<p class="mt-1 text-[10px] italic text-slate-500">The built-in norm table ships empty on purpose — a benchmark line renders only after each value is verified against its primary source (see the Benchmark workspace below). Until then, adding one politely refuses rather than showing an unverified number.</p>
<div class="mt-3 flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
<span class="text-xs text-slate-500">Present / export this view:</span>
<button id="lumen-present-trigger" class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold rounded-full text-white" style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#d97706,#ea580c);box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(234,88,12,0.3)">▶ Present</button>
<button class="px-2 py-1 text-xs rounded border border-slate-300 hover:bg-slate-50">Brief (HTML)</button>
<button class="px-2 py-1 text-xs rounded border border-slate-300 hover:bg-slate-50">Data (CSV)</button>
<label class="text-xs text-slate-600 flex items-center gap-1">
<input type="checkbox"/>Include identifiable data (FERPA)</label>
</div>
<button class="mt-3 text-xs underline text-slate-600" aria-expanded="false">🔬 Learn: “should I trust a trend?” sandbox</button>
<p class="mt-3 text-[10px] text-slate-700">Phase 1 — L1 default fires zero AI; dial up for gated, marked AI. Exports are FERPA-gated: both the brief and the CSV are finding-only unless you opt in to identifiable data, and formal exports require sign-off on any AI reading. docs/lumen_design.md.</p>
</div>"
`;

